---
alwaysApply: true
---

Always follow these rules when generating, editing, or refactoring code in this project:

1. Use TypeScript for all Playwright tests.

2. Follow Page Object Model (POM) structure:

-/pages for page objects

-/tests for test files

-/utils for helpers

-/fixtures if needed

3. Use async/await for all Playwright steps.

4. All selectors must be data-test-id or role-based when possible.

5. Never hardcode waits. Use proper Playwright assertions.

6. Test names must be descriptive and clear.

7. Always generate code that is readable, commented, and consistent.

8. Organize the project inside a parent folder named playwright-JS-framework.
